## 🔧 Utilities — `src/utils/`

| File | Key Exports / Description |
|---|---|
| `logger.js` | Winston-backed logger with daily rotating file transports (`logs/error-*.log`, `logs/combined-*.log`) + colored console output. Custom aesthetic methods: `ascii()`, `header()`, `section()`, `item()`, `table()`, `box()`, `divider()`, `blank()`, `loader()` (returns `{ done(), fail() }` for progress display). |
| `env.ts` | Zod validation of `.env`. Exports `env` (typed) and `getMongoURI()`. |
| `registry.js` | In-memory gacha item cache loaded from MongoDB on startup. Exports: `initializeRegistry()`, `getItem(name)`, `getCharacter(name)`, `getWeapon(name)`, `getAllCharacters()`, `getAllWeapons()`. |
| `env.js` | Compiled JS output of `env.ts` |
| `adminCheck.js` | Utility to validate if a user is in the `adminIds` list |
| `cooldowns.js` | Per-command cooldown tracking map |
| `colors.js` | Color constants / palette helpers |
| `images.js` | Image URL builders and asset helpers |
| `promo.js` | Promo card construction utilities |

---

## 📦 Commands — `src/commands/`

Commands are organized by category folder. Each file exports: `name`, `execute`, and optionally `aliases`, `description`, `usage`, `cooldown`.

| Category | Commands |
|---|---|
| `admin/` | Admin-only tools (user management, data editing, broadcaster controls, etc.) |
| `battle/` | RPG combat system (battle initiation, team selection, etc.) |
| `economy/` | Currency commands (`daily`, `weekly`, `work`, `balance`, `leaderboard`) |
| `expressions/` | Social/reaction commands (hug, kiss, pat, slap, etc.) — largest category (~19 files) |
| `gambling/` | Gambling games (`coinflip`, `slots`, `blackjack`, `rps`) |
| `general/` | Utility commands (`help`, `ping`, `profile`, `info`, etc.) |
| `meme/` | Meme generation commands |
| `pokemon/` | Pokémon-themed commands (likely for the hunting/zoo system) |
| `profile/` | User profile card display |
| `slash/` | Discord slash command definitions (registered via `deployCommands()`) |

---

## 🗄️ Repositories — `src/repositories/`

Thin abstraction layer over Mongoose models, following the Repository Pattern. Separates raw DB queries from service-level logic.

| File | Description |
|---|---|
| `UserRepository.ts` | Basic CRUD for User documents |
| `CharacterRepository.ts` | Basic CRUD for Character documents |
| `AnimalRepository.ts` | Basic CRUD for AnimalRegistry documents |

